verses.text_plain: I will love thee, O Lord, my strength.
verses.verse_html: 1I will love thee, O Lord, my strength.

verses.text_plain: The Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my buckler, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower.
verses.verse_html:
2The Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my buckler, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower. ▼
▼ my strength: Heb. my rock

footnotes.body_html: ▼ my strength: Heb. my rock

verses.text_plain: I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised: so shall I be saved from mine enemies.
verses.verse_html: 3I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised: so shall I be saved from mine enemies.

verses.text_plain: The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.
verses.verse_html:
4The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid. ▼
▼ ungodly men: Heb. Belial

footnotes.body_html: ▼ ungodly men: Heb. Belial

verses.text_plain: The sorrows of hell compassed me about: the snares of death prevented me.
verses.verse_html:
5The sorrows of hell compassed me about: the snares of death prevented me. ▼
▼ sorrows: or, cords

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sorrows: or, cords

verses.text_plain: In my distress I called upon the Lord, and cried unto my God: he heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him, even into his ears.
verses.verse_html: 6In my distress I called upon the Lord, and cried unto my God: he heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him, even into his ears.

verses.text_plain: Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken, because he was wroth.
verses.verse_html: 7Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken, because he was wroth.

verses.text_plain: There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.
verses.verse_html:
8There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it. ▼
▼ out of his nostrils: Heb. by his, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ out of his nostrils: Heb. by his, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ out of his nostrils: Heb. by his, etc

verses.text_plain: He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness was under his feet.
verses.verse_html: 9He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness was under his feet.

verses.text_plain: And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly: yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.
verses.verse_html: 10And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly: yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.

verses.text_plain: He made darkness his secret place; his pavilion round about him were dark waters and thick clouds of the skies.
verses.verse_html: 11He made darkness his secret place; his pavilion round about him were dark waters and thick clouds of the skies.

verses.text_plain: At the brightness that was before him his thick clouds passed, hail stones and coals of fire.
verses.verse_html: 12At the brightness that was before him his thick clouds passed, hail stones and coals of fire.

verses.text_plain: The Lord also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail stones and coals of fire.
verses.verse_html: 13The Lord also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail stones and coals of fire.

verses.text_plain: Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings, and discomfited them.
verses.verse_html: 14Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings, and discomfited them.

verses.text_plain: Then the channels of waters were seen, and the foundations of the world were discovered at thy rebuke, O Lord, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.
verses.verse_html: 15Then the channels of waters were seen, and the foundations of the world were discovered at thy rebuke, O Lord, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.

verses.text_plain: He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters.
verses.verse_html:
16He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters. ▼
▼ many: or, great

footnotes.body_html: ▼ many: or, great

verses.text_plain: He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me.
verses.verse_html: 17He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me.

tokens.text: me: for they were too strong

verses.text_plain: They prevented me in the day of my calamity: but the Lord was my stay.
verses.verse_html: 18They prevented me in the day of my calamity: but the Lord was my stay.

verses.text_plain: He brought me forth also into a large place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.
verses.verse_html: 19He brought me forth also into a large place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.

verses.text_plain: The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.
verses.verse_html: 20The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.

verses.text_plain: For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.
verses.verse_html: 21For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.

verses.text_plain: For all his judgments were before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.
verses.verse_html: 22For all his judgments were before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.

tokens.text: before me, and I did not put away

verses.text_plain: I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity.
verses.verse_html:
23I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity. ▼
▼ before: Heb. with

footnotes.body_html: ▼ before: Heb. with

verses.text_plain: Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.
verses.verse_html:
24Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight. ▼
▼ in…: Heb. before his eyes

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: Heb. before his eyes

verses.text_plain: With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful; with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright;
verses.verse_html: 25With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful; with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright;

verses.text_plain: With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself froward.
verses.verse_html:
26With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself froward. ▼
▼ shew thyself froward: or, wrestle

footnotes.body_html: ▼ shew thyself froward: or, wrestle

verses.text_plain: For thou wilt save the afflicted people; but wilt bring down high looks.
verses.verse_html: 27For thou wilt save the afflicted people; but wilt bring down high looks.

verses.text_plain: For thou wilt light my candle: the Lord my God will enlighten my darkness.
verses.verse_html:
28For thou wilt light my candle: the Lord my God will enlighten my darkness. ▼
▼ candle: or, lamp

footnotes.body_html: ▼ candle: or, lamp

verses.text_plain: For by thee I have run through a troop; and by my God have I leaped over a wall.
verses.verse_html:
29For by thee I have run through a troop; and by my God have I leaped over a wall. ▼
▼ run…: or, broken

tokens.text: For by thee I have run through

footnotes.body_html: ▼ run…: or, broken

verses.text_plain: As for God, his way is perfect: the word of the Lord is tried: he is a buckler to all those that trust in him.
verses.verse_html:
30As for God, his way is perfect: the word of the Lord is tried: he is a buckler to all those that trust in him. ▼
▼ tried: or, refined

footnotes.body_html: ▼ tried: or, refined

verses.text_plain: For who is God save the Lord? or who is a rock save our God?
verses.verse_html: 31For who is God save the Lord? or who is a rock save our God?

verses.text_plain: It is God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.
verses.verse_html: 32It is God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.

verses.text_plain: He maketh my feet like hinds’ feet, and setteth me upon my high places.
verses.verse_html: 33He maketh my feet like hinds’ feet, and setteth me upon my high places.

verses.text_plain: He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.
verses.verse_html: 34He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation: and thy right hand hath holden me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great.
verses.verse_html:
35Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation: and thy right hand hath holden me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great. ▼
▼ thy gentleness…: or, with thy meekness thou hast multiplied me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy gentleness…: or, with thy meekness thou hast multiplied me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy gentleness…: or, with thy meekness thou hast multiplied me

verses.text_plain: Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.
verses.verse_html:
36Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip. ▼
▼ my feet: Heb. mine ankles

footnotes.body_html: ▼ my feet: Heb. mine ankles

verses.text_plain: I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.
verses.verse_html: 37I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.

tokens.text: them: neither did I turn again

verses.text_plain: I have wounded them that they were not able to rise: they are fallen under my feet.
verses.verse_html: 38I have wounded them that they were not able to rise: they are fallen under my feet.

tokens.text: them that they were not able

verses.text_plain: For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.
verses.verse_html:
39For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me. ▼
▼ subdued: Heb. caused to bow

tokens.text: under me those that rose up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ subdued: Heb. caused to bow

verses.text_plain: Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.
verses.verse_html: 40Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.

verses.text_plain: They cried, but there was none to save them: even unto the Lord, but he answered them not.
verses.verse_html: 41They cried, but there was none to save them: even unto the Lord, but he answered them not.

verses.text_plain: Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.
verses.verse_html: 42Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people; and thou hast made me the head of the heathen: a people whom I have not known shall serve me.
verses.verse_html: 43Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people; and thou hast made me the head of the heathen: a people whom I have not known shall serve me.

verses.text_plain: As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me.
verses.verse_html:
44As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me. ▼
▼ As soon…: Heb. At the hearing of the ear
 , ▼
▼ submit…: or, yield feigned obedience
 , ▼
▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger

footnotes.body_text: ▼ As soon…: Heb. At the hearing of the ear
footnotes.body_html: ▼ As soon…: Heb. At the hearing of the ear
▼ submit…: or, yield feigned obedience

footnotes.body_text: ▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger
footnotes.body_html: ▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger

verses.text_plain: The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places.
verses.verse_html:
45The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places. ▼
▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger

footnotes.body_text: ▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger
footnotes.body_html: ▼ strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger

verses.text_plain: The Lord liveth; and blessed be my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 46The Lord liveth; and blessed be my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.

verses.text_plain: It is God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me.
verses.verse_html:
47It is God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me. ▼
▼ avengeth: Heb. giveth avengements for
 , ▼
▼ subdueth: or, destroyeth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ avengeth: Heb. giveth avengements for
▼ subdueth: or, destroyeth

verses.text_plain: He delivereth me from mine enemies: yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.
verses.verse_html:
48He delivereth me from mine enemies: yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man. ▼
▼ violent…: Heb. man of violence

footnotes.body_html: ▼ violent…: Heb. man of violence

verses.text_plain: Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O Lord, among the heathen, and sing praises unto thy name.
verses.verse_html:
49Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O Lord, among the heathen, and sing praises unto thy name. ▼
▼ give…: or, confess

footnotes.body_html: ▼ give…: or, confess

verses.text_plain: Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.
verses.verse_html: 50Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.
